Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
defStreamOutCheckUncolored(25.10)            defStreamOutCheckUncolored(25.10)

Name
       defStreamOutCheckUncolored

Syntax
        defStreamOutCheckUncolored {true 1 false 0 metal_only}

       Type: enum

       Default: false

       true above N5 nodes and metal_only for N5 and below nodes

       Specifies how to check and ignore uncolored shapes on DPT layers during
       DEF out and stream out.

              * true   1:   defOut   and   streamOut   will   go  through  all
                wires/vias/physical pins first. If the related layer  has  the
                definition  for  the  "MASK" and "SAMEMASK" rules, tool checks
                the object if a color should be assigned.

              * false 0: Ignores to check the uncolored object.

              * metal_only: Only checks the  color  on  the  metal  (including
                wires, physical pins, and top/bottom layer of vias).

Related Information
              * defOut

              * streamOut

